{
  "texts": [
    "For example, DL is often used in computer vision, where a computer analyzes images.",
    "In clinical genetics, DL may be used to \"classify\" (categorize) facial images to see what genetic condition a person may have based on their appearance [8,28].",
    "In general, to accomplish this, the DL model will be trained on many facial images, including images of people with different genetic conditions.",
    "At first, the model learns to identify simple things, like the edges of the face versus the background.",
    "More layers allow increased complexity, such as the ability to detect different parts of the face (e.g., the mouth, nose, and eyes)."
  ]
}